<p>To adapt to Google's latest search engine update, focus on expert-led content that satisfies user intent, optimize site speed and mobile experience, and expand visibility across AI assistants, voice platforms, and local searches. Prioritize continuous audits over quick fixes to secure sustainable rankings. This expert-first approach aligns with Google's AI-driven E-A-T requirements and positions your brand for long-term success.</p>

<p><strong>The search landscape has shifted once again.</strong> On June 30, 2025, Google announced the rollout of its June 2025 core update. This is the second major algorithm change this year following the March update. With an expected three-week rollout period (longer than the usual two weeks), this update is already creating significant ripples across search rankings worldwide.</p>

<p>As digital marketing specialists who've successfully navigated countless algorithm changes, we at Digital Visibility understand the anxiety these updates can create. Our <a href="/services/digital-marketing/">SEO+AEO+GEO optimization strategies</a> have helped clients achieve #1, #2, and #3 rankings in just one week, and we're here to help you understand what this latest update means for your business.</p>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What You'll Learn From This Blog</h2>

<p>This comprehensive guide will walk you through everything you need to know about adapting to Google's June 2025 core update:</p>

<ul>
<li>Why this core update shifts the SEO landscape and what it means for your visibility</li>
<li>How to overhaul your content strategy to meet AI-powered ranking signals</li>
<li>Technical tweaks that boost speed, user experience, and Core Web Vitals</li>
<li>Ways to extend reach across voice search, AI assistants, and local discovery</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="what-is-june-2025-update" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What is Google's June 2025 Core Update?</h2>

<p>Google's June 2025 core update started on June 30, 2025, at 7:34 AM PDT. This is the second major algorithm change of 2025, following the March update that ended on March 27. The rollout will take three weeks to complete, which is longer than the usual two weeks.</p>

<p>Unlike targeted updates that address specific issues like spam or product reviews, core updates involve broad changes to Google's ranking systems. These updates are designed to improve Google's ability to surface helpful, high-quality content in search. They don't target specific websites or punish bad content. Instead, they help Google find and show better content that answers what people are looking for.</p>

