<h2 id="technical-tweaks" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What technical tweaks can boost your performance?</h2>

<p>Technical excellence is non-negotiable under Google's updated metrics. With the update's emphasis on user experience, businesses must ensure their websites meet Google's technical standards.</p>

<p>Think of your site as a sports car. No matter how great the engine, it won't win races if the wheels are flat.</p>

<p>Essential technical improvements include:</p>

<ul>
<li>Implement mobile-first responsive design that feels native on any device</li>
<li>Optimize page speed: compress images, defer scripts, and leverage caching</li>
<li>Monitor and improve Core Web Vitals: Largest Contentful Paint, Interaction to Next Paint, Cumulative Layout Shift</li>
<li>Apply schema markup for rich results and AI visibility</li>
</ul>

<p>Google recently replaced First Input Delay (FID) with Interaction to Next Paint (INP), making website speed and responsiveness even more important. Your website should load in under 3 seconds and work perfectly on mobile phones.</p>

